\section{Random Numbers and Javascript}


Before we start let me be absolutely clear. Only nature can produce truly random events! Any computer would produce random numbers, based on algorithms and it will come pretty close, so wherever you read in this article the word random, I actually mean pseudo-random. We will start with refreshing your memory about the Math.random() and we will end calculating the value of \\(\pi\\) using a {{wi:Monte Carlo}} simulation and a bunch of needles!

